The Future Mind team is looking for a self-reliant iOS Developer to join us in Warsaw.

If you are an experienced, reliable software engineer, ready to lead a team of developers, able to meet business requirements and take responsibility for the finished product in each given project, take a look at what we have to offer. The job is all about solving problems, sharing knowledge, and being a part of the team. We work for companies such as Virgin, EY, ≈ªabka, Nespresso, Morizon, EcoCar, Livespace, Envelo, Empik, Packhelp, and SkyCash.

While working with us you will:
create iOS applications for some interesting global brands and startups,
design and establish communication with server data sources,
create user interfaces based on mock-ups prepared by UI/UX experts,
work with some of our existing applications to further develop and optimize them,
test the effects of your work and review the work of your team,
take part in preparing relevant project documentation,
assume responsibility for the technical side of your projects.

We require you to:
have at least 3 years of commercial experience in programming iOS applications,
have a solid knowledge of Swift and hopefully some Objective-C too (but don't expect to use it too often),
speak English at a level which will allow you to communicate with clients and peers and read specs,
be creative ‚Äî good ideas and constructive remarks are always welcome!
be communicative ‚Äî we want you to interact with the people you work with, help them do a better job,
pay attention to details, be consistent and accurate.

We appreciate:
experience gained from completing your own projects, not only commercial stuff,
knowledge of Agile methodologies and project tools,
people who have their own passions and hobbies, and preferably who like to sail (we do, every summer).

We offer:
frequently reviewed salary relevant to market rates, your skills, and the results you achieve,
the possibility to significantly impact your projects ‚Äî you are the team leader and your input has real value,
opportunity to work with clients from all over the world on a variety of tasks ‚Äî each project is different,
continuous professional development and application of new technologies ‚Äî we all keep learning,
financial support when you want to learn, go to a conference or take part in a meetup,
flexible working hours and the ability to partially work remotely,
private health insurance and sports membership,
coffee, tea, fruit and snacks at work,
chill-out space, foosball and some gaming gear for when you need to relax.

Who we are? 

MAX is a Swedish family brand. MAX are delicious burgers of the highest quality. MAX is a wide selection of veg and vegan products. managing, support, operations and restaurant development issues within the IT unit, 
continuously managing various types of IT projects (such as: client management and IT development at new restaurants) as well as selected internal processes. 
cooperating with IT Group in Sweden (25 people) and reporting what's going on in Poland to the Deputy CEO  
cooperating with local IT suppliers

You'll have to familiarize yourself with the Group's technical environments so that you have an overall broad technical understanding and depth. 
You will work in multinational environment so your English is expected to be very good. 
You need you to be very flexible to cooperate with other countries  (mostly scandinavian).
Solid experience in IT technology in IT infrastructure, architecture, communication (10 years +)

Accustomed to leading and working with teams and used to steering these to a coordinated delivery, focusing on results. (5 years +)
Ability to support with hands on IT related questions from time to time.

You‚Äôll be one of a few, so your impact will be felt inside and outside the company. You‚Äôll be working on a product that is used by thousands of users located all around the globe.

What you‚Äôll be doing?

Multisport cards, private health care & benefit platform

In today‚Äôs software-centric economy, speed is everything. The pressure to deliver more, faster, falls squarely on development teams. Sauce Labs accelerates software development by removing testing as a bottleneck. Our automated testing cloud ensures that the web and mobile applications people use everyday work flawlessly on any browser or device.

Before Sauce, testing took too long, it was tedious and expensive to maintain, and it took the focus off of innovation and shifted it to annoying infrastructure issues. With Sauce, innovators accelerate their software development cycles, improve quality, deploy with confidence and reduce costs. We call that automated testing. But you‚Äôll probably just call it awesome.

The Role:

Feature teams implement new ideas and improve existing ones based on the vision of the Product Team and feedback from our customers.

Web Platform has high visibility and importance within the company as it's job is to provide common foundations for those teams to build on, merge and deployment strategy, monitoring, CI/CD pipelines and give technological guidance to front-end developers throughout the company.

Fun and relaxed work environment
